explanation:
## Concept
Demand paging loads pages into memory only when accessed, reducing initial memory footprint.

## Implementation
```c
// Page fault handler
if (!page_in_memory(virtual_address)) {
    load_page_from_disk(virtual_address);
    restart_instruction();
}
```

## Trade-offs
- **Pros**: Lower memory usage, faster startup
- **Cons**: Page fault latency, thrashing

## Pitfalls
- Thrashing under memory pressure
- Working set estimation errors
